    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-05-24T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-05-24T23:00:00-05:00" n="458"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4378: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-25T12:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 25, 1922—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received May 25—5:53 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>232. My 228, May 23, 11 a.m.<note n="45" xml:id="d458fn45">Not printed.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">Albany</hi> reenforcement Legation Guard left to-day.</p>
                <p>Chang Tso-lin with 30,000 men entrenching between Chinwangtao and Shanhaikwan and
                    declares will fight. Believe that Wu will soon compel them to follow their
                    comrades beyond wall. That done <hi rend="italic">Albany</hi> no longer
                    necessary on account civil war.</p>
                <p>Huston telegraphs as follows: “May 23, 10 a.m. Ten thousand Chen’s troops from
                    Kwangsi stationed outskirts Canton have declared themselves independent and
                    threaten city, demand reinstatement of Chen as Commander in Chief. Wei
                        Pang-ping<note n="45a" xml:id="d458fn45a">Commander, Third Division,
                        Kwangtung army.</note> wields real power in the city.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
